@realmoney Thought for The Day Discounted divided models weigh the suppression of short term Treasuries (basically zero up to two years) and the Fed's support of credit spreads (across the quality spectrum) - more than a 2-3 quarter loss of profitability.

Basically the risk free rate of return, or discount rate in the calculation of the present value of futures earnings creates a PE multiplier with most fundy assumptions above the pre crisis level. This means if EPS return to anything near earnings power, it is not hard to see a

"Tina Ripper." Combine this with a more limited supply of equities (more than halving from 2009) often discussed on @realmoney - we have a potential large imbalance between demand and supply down the road.
